sentences: Joseph Marie Alphonse Nicolas Jongen (14 December 1873 – 12 July 1953) was a Belgian organist, composer, and music educator.
On the strength of an amazing precocity for music, he was admitted to the Liège Conservatoire at the extraordinarily young age of seven, and spent the next sixteen years there.
Jongen won a First Prize for Fugue in 1895, an honors diploma in piano the next year, and another for organ in 1896.
